# Local Development Environment Variables
# Copy this file to .dev.vars and fill in your actual values.
#
# ⚡ AUTO-DISCOVERY FEATURE:
# The gen-wrangler.js script automatically discovers ALL placeholder keys from
# wrangler.jsonc (any ${PLACEHOLDER} pattern), so you don't need to manually
# update this file when adding new placeholders - just add the KEY=value pair!
#
# 📋 CURRENT PLACEHOLDERS:
# The following variables are currently used in wrangler.jsonc:

CORS_ALLOWED_ORIGINS=*
KV_ID=your_kv_id_here

# 🆕 ADDING NEW VARIABLES:
# 1. Add ${YOUR_NEW_VAR} to wrangler.jsonc
# 2. Add YOUR_NEW_VAR=value_here below
# 3. Run: npm run preview (to test)
# 4. For CI/CD deployments, you'll need to add:
# - STAGING_YOUR_NEW_VAR (for staging environment)
# - PRODUCTION_YOUR_NEW_VAR (for production environment)

